Spokesperson of the Kwara state Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) Tunde Ashaolu is dead. Ashaolu died on Sunday evening 24 hours after celebrating his 50th birthday anniversary. The late politician was said to have died of heart seizure in Abuja. Former Senate President Bukola Saraki was said to have to have hosted Ashaolu and erstwhile chairman of Ekiti local government area of the state, to a get-together in Abuja their birthdays anniversary. The ruling All Progressives Congress (APC) in the state has commiserated with the opposition PDP.   2022: Ekiti APC woman leader is Deputy Gov candidate     Why Oyebanji is likely to win Ekiti governorship poll     Lagos PDP holds state congress   APC described the death of PDP’s spokesperson as saddening and unfortunate. In a statement, APC’s Spokesperson Tajudeen Folaranmi acknowledged that the late PDP’s spokesperson gave himself to the patriotic task of deepening the political conversation in the state. “We also commiserate with members of the deceased family whom the late Ashaolu has left behind. “We pray with a fervency that the PDP family and the members of the immediate family of the deceased will find the fortitude to bear the loss and strength to carry on in this tragic moment,” the statement reads.